  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to investigate whether disease progression in patients with chronic heart
      failure (CHF) can be assessed by new biomarkers, and determine their diagnostic value. The
      study also intends to describe comparison of echocardiography with cardiopulmonary function
      test in CHF patients, and relating these cardiac functional parameters to clinical outcome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
